i\n* 2019\u2013present [[Toyota Supra#J29|J29]] Toyota Supra (Japanese ''SZ-R'' models)\n* 2019-present [[BMW Z4 (G29)|G29]] Z4 Sdrive30i\n* 2020-present [[Morgan Plus Four]]\n\n=== 225 kW version ===\nThis engine features a reinforced crankshaft with larger main bearings and new pistons with a lower 9.5:1 compression ratio. This allows the engine to take more boost pressure from a larger turbocharger, which blows compressed air through a reworked intake tract.<ref>{{cite web\n |last        =Nishimoto\n |first       =Alex\n |date        =7 September 2018\n |url=https://www.motortrend.com/news/2019-bmw-x2-m35i-debuts-302-hp-turbo-four/\n |title=2019 BMW X2 M35i Debuts With 302-HP Turbo-Four\n |website=[[Motor Trend]]\n |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> Revealed in May 2019, this engine is shared with the new MINI Countryman JCW, Clubman JCW<ref>{{Cite web\n |last1       =Bode\n |first1      =Matthias\n |last2       =Lampka\n |first2      =Andreas\n |date        =15 May 2019\n |url=https://www.press.bmwgroup.com/global/article/detail/T0295639EN/\n |title=The new MINI John Cooper Works Clubman and the new MINI John Cooper Works Countryman.\n |website=[[BMW|BMW Group]]\n |language=en\n |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref> and JCW GP models<ref name=\"gpfinal-group\">{{cite web\n |last1       =Bode\n |first1      =Matthias\n |last2       =Lampka\n |first2      =Andreas\n |date        =20 November 2019\n |url         =https://www.press.bmwgroup.com/usa/article/detail/T0302824EN_US/\n |title       =The new MINI John Cooper Works GP.\n |website     =[[BMW|BMW Group]]\n |access-date =9 April 2020\n}}</ref>. The engine output increased by {{convert|55|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and torque increased to {{convert|450|Nm|ftlb|0|abbr=on}}.\n\n* 2019\u2013present [[BMW X2 (F39)|F39]] X2 M35i\n* 2019\u2013present [[BMW 1 Series (F40)|F40]] M135i xDrive\n* 2019\u2013present [[Mini Clubman (2007)|F54]] Clubman JCW\n* 2019\u2013present [[Mini Countryman|F60]] Countryman JCW\n* 2019\u2013present [[BMW 2 Series (F44)|F44]] M235i xDrive Gran Coup\u00e9\n* 2020\u2013present [[Mini Hatch#Mini John Cooper Works GP (2020)|F56]] MINI John Cooper Works GP\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{BMW automotive petrol engines: 2000s to 2010s}}\n\n[[Category:BMW engines|B48]]\n[[Category:Products introduced in 2014]]\n[[Category:Inline-four engines]]\n[[Category:Gasoline engines by model]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Turbocharged inline-four petrol engine}}\n{{Infobox automobile engine\n| name = BMW B48\n| image = BMW B48 im BMW-Museum 2018-06.jpg \n| manufacturer = [[BMW]]\n| aka =\n| production = 2014\u2013present\n| predecessor = [[BMW N20]]\n| successor =\n| configuration = [[Inline-four engine|Inline-four]]\n| displacement = {{convert|1998|cc|cuin|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| bore = {{convert|82.0|mm|abbr=on|lk=on}}\n| stroke = {{convert|94.6|mm|abbr=on}}\n| block = \n| head = \n| valvetrain = [[DOHC]]\n| compression = 11:1\n| supercharger =\n| turbocharger = Single [[Turbocharger#Twin-scroll|twin-scroll]]\n| fuelsystem = [[Fuel injection#Direct injection|Direct injection]]\n| management =\n| fueltype = [[Gasoline engine|Petrol]] \n| oilsystem =\n| coolingsystem =\n| power =\n| specpower =\n| torque =\n| length =\n| width =\n| height =\n| diameter =\n| weight =\n}}\n\n[[File:BMW_B48_installed_in_a_2014_MINI_Cooper_S-_2014-08-17_17-24.jpg|thumb|right|B48 in a 2014 MINI Cooper S]]\n\nThe [[BMW]] '''B48''' is a [[turbocharged]] [[inline-four engine|inline-four]] [[gasoline|petrol]] engine which replaced the [[BMW N20]] and has been in production since 2014. It was first used in the [[Mini_Hatch#Second_generation_(R56/57)_(2006\u20132013)|F56 Mini Hatch]] and has been used in BMW applications since 2015.\n\nThe B48 is part of a modular BMW engine family of 3-cylinder ([[BMW B38|B38]]/ [[BMW B37|B37]]), 4-cylinder (B48/ [[BMW B47|B47]]) and 6-cylinder ([[BMW B58|B58]]) engines,<ref>{{cite web|title=BMW modular engines: B37, B38, B47 and B48|url=http://www.bmwblog.com/2014/05/21/bmw-modular-engines-b37-b38-b47-b48/|website=www.bmwblog.com|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> which use a displacement of {{convert|500|cc|cuin|1|abbr=on}} per cylinder.\n\n== Design ==\nCompared with its N20 predecessor, the B48 uses a more [[undersquare]] design.<ref>{{cite web|title=Watch out for the B's \u2013 Comparing the upcoming B48 2.0 liter turbo four-cylinder to the N20 it will replace|url=http://www.bimmerboost.com/content.php?5490-Watch-out-for-the-B-s-Comparing-the-upcoming-B48-2-0-liter-turbo-four-cylinder-to-the-N20-it-will-replace-Bore-x-stroke-specifications|website=www.bimmerboost.com|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> As per the N20, the block and head are made from [[aluminium]].<ref>{{cite web|title=2016 BMW X1 first drive review|url=http://www.caranddriver.com/reviews/2016-bmw-x1-xdrive28i-first-drive-review|website=www.caranddriver.com|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref> Other features shared with the N20 include a twin-scroll turbocharger, [[fuel injection#Direct injection|direct injection]], [[variable valve lift]] ([[Valvetronic]]) and variable valve timing (Double [[VANOS]]).<ref>{{cite web|title=BMW B48 Four Cylinder Turbocharged Engines|url=http://www.unixnerd.demon.co.uk/b48.html|website=www.unixnerd.demon.co.uk|accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Models ==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!Power!!Torque!!Years\n|-\n|{{convert|135|kW|hp|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} <br> at 5,000\u20136,500 [[Revolutions per minute|rpm]] ||{{convert|290|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on|lk=on}} <br> at 1,350\u20134,250 rpm || 2016\u2013\n|-\n|{{convert|144|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 4,700\u20136,000 rpm ||{{convert|280|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,250\u20134,500 rpm || 2014\u2013\n|-\n|{{convert|165|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 5,000\u20136,500 rpm ||{{convert|310|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,400\u20135,000 rpm || 2016\u2013\n|-\n|{{convert|170|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 5,000\u20136,500 rpm ||{{convert|300|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,250\u20134,800 rpm || rowspan=\"2\" | 2015\u2013\n|-\n|{{convert|185|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 5,200\u20136,500 rpm ||{{convert|350|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,450\u20134,800 rpm \n|-\n|{{convert|190|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 5,000\u20136,500 rpm ||{{convert|400|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,550\u20134,400 rpm || 2016\u2013\n|-\n|{{convert|225|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 5,000\u20136,250 rpm ||{{convert|450|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} <br> at 1,750\u20134,500 rpm || 2019\u2013\n|}\n\n=== 135 kW version ===\nWhen combined with the electric motor, the 330e and 530e overall output is {{convert|185|kW|hp|0|abbr=on}} and {{convert|420|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}<ref>http://www.bmw.com/com/en/newvehicles/3series/sedan/2015/showroom/technical_data.html#m=330e</ref>\n<ref>http://www.bmw.com/com/en/newvehicles/5series/sedan/2015/showroom/technical_data.html#m=530e</ref>\n\nApplications:\n* 2015\u20132019 [[BMW 3 Series (F30)|F30/F31/F34]] 320i\n* 2016\u20132018 [[BMW F30|F30]] 330e\n* 2016\u20132019 [[BMW F20|F20]] 120i\n* 2016-present [[BMW F32|F33|F36]] 420i\n* 2018\u2013present [[BMW X3 (G01)|G01]] X3 xDrive20i\n\n* 2018\u2013present [[BMW X4 (G02)|G02]] X4 xDrive20i\n* 2019\u2013present [[BMW 3 Series (G20)|G20]] 320i\n* 2019\u2013present [[BMW 3 Series (G20)|G20]] 330e\n* 2017\u2013present [[BMW 5 Series (G30)|G30]] 530e\n\n=== 144 kW version ===  \nIn the MINI Cooper S, a temporary overboost increases peak torque by {{convert|20|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}} to {{convert|300|Nm|lbft|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite web|title=BMW\u2019s new B48 2.0 litre four-cylinder TwinPower Turbo engine to produce up to 255 hp and 400 Nm|url=http://paultan.org/2014/02/25/bmws-new-2-0-litre-twinpower-turbo-engine-255hp-400nm/|website=www.paultan.org|accessdate=16 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nApplications:\n* 2014\u2013present [[Mini Hatch#Third generation (F56) (2014)(B46: 2015-present) |F56]] MINI Cooper S<ref>{{cite web|title=MINI\u2019s Prince Engine is Dead- enter the B37 & B48|url=http://www.motoringfile.com/2013/09/05/minis-prince-eng